I would like to see the ability to use the {blog-posts} macro (or perhaps a new macro suited especially to this purpose) to display blog posts from multiple spaces.

Some examples of where this would be useful:

* Having a single page in confluence that displays all blog-posts happening across the organization
   {blog-posts:spaces=@all}

* Aggregating several users' posts into a single display
   {blog-posts:spaces=~msmith,~djohnson,~bbrown}

* Displaying all blog posts that have the label 'java' across all spaces.
   {blog-posts:spaces=@all,labels=java}

* For backward compatibility, omitting the 'spaces' attribute would continue to pull in the blog posts from the space in which the macro is being used:
   {blog-posts}
   or, to be explicit:
   {blog-posts:spaces=@self}

* Displaying all blog posts with the labels 'java' and/or 'orm' from each of the personal spaces of the members of the 'development-team' group:
    {blog-posts:groups=development-team|labels=java,orm}

