Numbered lists are rendered with different amounts of whitespace to normal text, causing unnecessarily misaligned panels, column and lists. Specifically, numbered lists need more whitespace when used beneath a title so that they appear at the same pixel height on the screen.

This is most noticable when using columns or panels containing numbered lists. It would be great if the amount of whitespace could match normal text of the same size, if possible.

To replicate:

{section}
{column:width=50%}
h3. Level 3 Heading
# Numbered List Item
# Numbered List Item
{column}
{column:width=50%}
h3. Level 3 Heading
Normal Text
Normal Text
{column}
{section}
\\
\\
{panel}
# Numero Uno
# Numero Duo
{panel}

{panel}
Line A
Line B
{panel}

