This feature request would greatly add to the usability of Confluence for less technical users.

We would like to be able to easily add a pulldown to the edit toolbar that could contain plugins or macros.

As an example, we added the Table of Contents plugin that allows you to auto-generate a TOC from the headings in the document. The "command word" for this is: {toc}

It would be nice if this could be added to a pulldown in the edit toolbar so users could easily see what extened functionality was available from plugins or macros. In the toolbar it would use a descriptive word such as "Table of Contents" and when selected would add "{toc}" into the document for them.

Optionally you could create and assign this to a new icon on the edit toolbar instead of a text pulldown.

Also, it would be nice if the plugin SDK was extended to allow plugins to have an option for adding an icon/pulldown text. If the plugin had this option, it would show up in the admin/plugins panel as maybe checkboxs ("show icon on edit toolbar" / choose an icon) and/or ("show in pulldown" \ "Pulldown text: ").

Being able to extend the edit toolbar in this way would make editing much easier- and because you will always/ know/remember what functionality is available to you, make better pages in the process.

